SIMPLE: unquestioned
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unquestioned
<hw>Un*ques"tioned</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
called in question; not doubted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not interrogated; having no questions asked; not
examined or examined into.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She muttering prayers, as holy rites she meant,⟦br⟧
Through the divided crowd <qex>unquestioned</qex> went.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Indisputable; not to be opposed or
impugned.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their <qex>unquestioned</qex> pleasures must be served.</q>
<rj><qau>B. Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unquick</ent>⟦br⟧
